## API Translation Reference

### Selectors

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `cy.get('[data-test="x"]')` | `this.locator('[data-test="x"]')` (page object) |
| `cy.get('[data-test-id="x"]')` | `this.locator('[data-test-id="x"]')` (page object) |
| `cy.byTestID('x')` | `this.locator('[data-test="x"]')` |
| `cy.byLegacyTestID('x')` | `this.locator('[data-test-id="x"]')` |
| `cy.byTestRows('resource-row')` | `this.locator('[data-test-rows="resource-row"]')` |
| `cy.byButtonText('Save')` | `this.page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Save' })` |
| `cy.contains('text')` | `this.page.getByText('text')` or `this.locator('selector', { hasText: 'text' })` |
| `cy.contains('selector', 'text')` | `this.locator('selector', { hasText: 'text' })` or `this.locator('selector').filter({ hasText: 'text' })` |
| `cy.get('.pf-v6-c-table').find('tr')` | `this.locator('.pf-v6-c-table tr')` or compose with `.locator('tr')` |
| `cy.get('body').then($body => if...)` | `const count = await locator.count();` then branch |

### Actions

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `cy.get(s).click()` | `await this.robustClick(this.locator(s))` (page object) |
| `cy.get(s).click({ force: true })` | `await this.robustClick(this.locator(s), { force: true })` |
| `cy.get(s).type('text')` | `await this.locator(s).fill('text')` |
| `cy.get(s).clear().type('text')` | `await this.locator(s).fill('text')` (fill clears first) |
| `cy.get(s).select('option')` | `await this.locator(s).selectOption('option')` |
| `cy.get(s).check()` | `await this.locator(s).check()` |
| `cy.get(s).uncheck()` | `await this.locator(s).uncheck()` |
| `cy.get(s).scrollIntoView()` | `await this.locator(s).scrollIntoViewIfNeeded()` |
| `cy.get(s).within(() => { ... })` | `const container = this.locator(s); container.locator(child)` — scope via chained `.locator()` |
| `cy.get('input').attachFile(f)` | `await this.locator('input[type="file"]').setInputFiles(f)` |
| `cy.dropFile(selector, file)` | `await this.locator(selector).setInputFiles(filePath)` |

### Navigation

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `cy.visit('/path')` | `await this.goTo('/path')` (page object `navigate*` method) |
| `cy.visitVMs()` | Step driver calls page object's `navigateToVMList(namespace)` |
| `cy.visitCatalog()` | Step driver calls page object's `navigateToCatalog(namespace)` |
| `cy.clickNavLink(['Networking', 'NAD'])` | Page object sidebar navigation method |
| `cy.switchProject(ns)` | Step driver method wrapping project-switcher interaction |
| `cy.url().should('include', '/path')` | `await expect(this.page).toHaveURL(/\/path/)` |

### Assertions

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `cy.get(s).should('exist')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toBeAttached()` |
| `cy.get(s).should('not.exist')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).not.toBeAttached()` |
| `cy.get(s).should('be.visible')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toBeVisible()` |
| `cy.get(s).should('not.be.visible')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).not.toBeVisible()` |
| `cy.get(s).should('contain', 'text')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toContainText('text')` |
| `cy.get(s).should('contain.text', 'text')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toContainText('text')` |
| `cy.get(s).should('have.text', 'text')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toHaveText('text')` |
| `cy.get(s).should('have.value', 'v')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toHaveValue('v')` |
| `cy.get(s).should('be.disabled')` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toBeDisabled()` |
| `cy.get(s).should('have.length', n)` | `await expect(this.locator(s)).toHaveCount(n)` |
| `.and('contain', 'x')` | chain: `await expect(loc).toContainText('x')` (separate assertion) |
| `cy.title().should('include', 't')` | `await expect(this.page).toHaveTitle(/t/)` |

### Waits and Retries

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `cy.wait(3000)` | **AVOID.** Use `await expect(locator).toBeVisible()` or `waitForCondition()` instead. Only use `page.waitForTimeout()` as absolute last resort during debugging. |
| `cy.get(s, { timeout: 60000 })` | `await this.locator(s).waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout: 60000 })` |
| `cy.contains(text, { timeout })` | `await this.page.getByText(text).waitFor({ state: 'visible', timeout })` |
| `cy.intercept('GET', url).as('req')` + `cy.wait('@req')` | `await this.page.waitForResponse(url)` or `page.waitForResponse(resp => resp.url().includes(url))` |
| `waitForStatus(vm, 'Running', timeout)` | Step driver method using `waitForCondition()` with text-based or API-based polling |

### Resource Lifecycle

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `cy.exec('oc create ...')` | `KubernetesClient.createCustomResource(...)` via client step driver |
| `cy.exec('oc delete ...')` | `KubernetesClient.deleteCustomResource(...)` via client step driver |
| `cy.exec('oc get ... -o jsonpath')` | `KubernetesClient.getCustomResource(...)` |
| `cy.deleteResource(kind, name)` | Client step driver: `deleteResource(kind, name, namespace)` |
| `cy.deleteVM(name, ns)` | Client step driver: `deleteVirtualMachine(name, namespace)` |
| `cy.startVM(name, ns)` / `cy.stopVM` | Client step driver wrapping K8s patch operations |
| `cy.createExampleTemplate()` | Client step driver creating template via K8s API |

### Environment and Configuration

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `Cypress.env('NON_PRIV')` | `EnvVariables.nonPriv` or `TestConfigManager.getConfig()` |
| `Cypress.env('TEST_NS')` | `TestConfigManager.getConfig().testNamespace` |
| `Cypress.env('ARCH')` | `EnvVariables.arch` (add to `env-variables.ts` if missing) |
| `Cypress.env('GPU')` | `EnvVariables.gpu` (add if missing) |
| `adminOnlyDescribe(...)` | `test.describe(name, () => { test.skip(EnvVariables.nonPriv, 'Admin only'); ... })` |
| `adminOnlyIT(...)` | `test(name, () => { test.skip(EnvVariables.nonPriv, 'Admin only'); ... })` |
| `xit('disabled')` | `test.skip('reason', ...)` or `test.fixme(...)` with Jira link |

### Conditional Logic

| Cypress | Playwright |
|---------|-----------|
| `cy.get('body').then($body => { if ($body.find(s).length) { ... } })` | `if (await this.locator(s).count() > 0) { ... }` |
| `cy.get(s).then($el => { ... })` | `const text = await this.locator(s).textContent()` |
| Multiple `.then()` chains | Sequential `await` statements |

