## Structural Transformation Rules

### Rule 1: Flatten Sequential `it` Blocks into Self-Contained Tests

Cypress `testIsolation: false` means `it` blocks share browser state. In Playwright, each `test()` is isolated.

**Cypress pattern (anti-pattern for Playwright):**
```typescript
describe('VM lifecycle', () => {
  before(() => { cy.beforeSpec(); });
  it('create VM', () => { vm.create(data); });
  it('verify overview', () => { /* assumes VM exists from prior it */ });
  it('delete VM', () => { vm.delete(name); });
});
```

**Playwright equivalent:**
```typescript
test.describe('VM lifecycle', { tag: ['@tier1'] }, () => {
  test('ID(CNV-XXXXX) Verify VM overview after creation', async ({ page }) => {
    await withAllure({ suite: 'VM Lifecycle', feature: 'Tier 1', tags: ['@tier1'] });
    const vmDriver = VMStepDriver.Init(page);
    const loginDriver = LoginStepDriver.Init(page);

    await test.step('Login and create VM', async () => {
      await loginDriver.performKubeAdminLogin();
      await vmDriver.createVM(vmData);
    });

    await test.step('Verify overview tab', async () => {
      await vmDriver.navigateToOverview();
      await vmDriver.verifyOverviewFields(expectedData);
    });

    await test.step('Cleanup', async () => {
      await vmDriver.deleteVM(vmData.name, vmData.namespace);
    });
  });
});
```

### Rule 2: Replace `before`/`after` Hooks with `test.step` Blocks

Cypress hooks that create resources become explicit `test.step` blocks within each test, keeping tests self-contained.

**Exception:** `test.beforeEach` for login is acceptable when ALL tests in a describe need the same login. Prefer the `storageState` mechanism from global setup.

### Rule 3: Replace Custom Commands with Step Drivers

Every `cy.customCommand()` maps to a step driver method that wraps a page object interaction.

| Cypress custom command | Playwright equivalent |
|------------------------|----------------------|
| `cy.beforeSpec()` | `loginDriver.performKubeAdminLogin()` (or rely on `storageState`) |
| `cy.visitVMs()` | `vmListDriver.navigateToVMList(namespace)` |
| `cy.clickSaveBtn()` | `commons.clickSave()` (via `BasePage`) |
| `cy.checkTitle(title)` | `await expect(page.getByRole('heading', { name: title })).toBeVisible()` |

### Rule 4: Replace Fixed Waits with Condition-Based Waits

```typescript
// NEVER: cy.wait(5000) → page.waitForTimeout(5000)
// ALWAYS: condition-based
await expect(statusLocator).toContainText('Running', { timeout: 120_000 });
// or
await this.waitForCondition(async () => {
  const text = await statusLocator.textContent();
  return text?.includes('Running') ?? false;
}, TestTimeouts.CLUSTER_OPERATION);
```

### Rule 5: Replace `cy.exec('oc ...')` with KubernetesClient

All cluster interactions go through `KubernetesClient` via a client step driver — never shell commands in tests.

```typescript
// NEVER
cy.exec('oc delete vm test-vm -n test-ns');
// ALWAYS
await k8sDriver.deleteVirtualMachine('test-vm', 'test-ns');
```

### Rule 6: Replace `cy.get(...).within(...)` with Scoped Locators

```typescript
// Cypress
cy.get('[data-test="modal"]').within(() => {
  cy.get('[data-test="name"]').type('my-vm');
  cy.byButtonText('Submit').click();
});

// Playwright (page object method)
async fillModalForm(name: string): Promise<void> {
  const modal = this.locator('[data-test="modal"]');
  await modal.locator('[data-test="name"]').fill(name);
  await this.robustClick(modal.locator('button', { hasText: 'Submit' }));
}
```

### Rule 7: Handle Conditional Presence without `.then()`

```typescript
// Cypress
cy.get('body').then($body => {
  if ($body.find('[data-test="welcome"]').length > 0) {
    cy.get('[data-test="welcome"] button').click();
  }
});

// Playwright (page object)
async dismissWelcomeIfPresent(): Promise<void> {
  const welcome = this.locator('[data-test="welcome"]');
  if (await welcome.count() > 0) {
    await this.robustClick(welcome.locator('button'));
  }
}
```

### Rule 8: Map Cypress Retries to Playwright Retries

Cypress per-test `retries: { runMode: N }` becomes Playwright `test.describe.configure({ retries: N })` or is left to the global config. Never use per-test retries to mask flaky selectors — fix the root cause.

