## Migration Checklist

For each Cypress file being migrated:

- [ ] Read the entire Cypress test file and all imported views/constants
- [ ] Document each `it` block's intent in plain language
- [ ] Search existing page objects and step drivers for reusable methods
- [ ] Identify test isolation strategy (A, B, or C)
- [ ] Create/extend page objects with needed locators and methods
- [ ] Create/extend step drivers with needed workflow wrappers
- [ ] Write the spec file using project template
- [ ] Replace all `cy.wait()` with condition-based waits
- [ ] Replace all `cy.exec('oc ...')` with KubernetesClient calls
- [ ] Add `withAllure()` and proper tags
- [ ] Add `ID(TICKET-XXXXX)` to each test title
- [ ] Run `npx tsc --noEmit` — zero errors
- [ ] Run `npm run lint:fix` — clean
- [ ] Run tests with `PLAYWRIGHT_RETRIES=0` — passing
- [ ] Verify no orphaned resources after test run

## Things to NEVER Do

- **Never transliterate** — `cy.get(x).click()` → `page.locator(x).click()` is not a migration. Understand intent, use framework APIs.
- **Never use `page.waitForTimeout()`** as a replacement for `cy.wait()`. Find the condition to wait for.
- **Never put locators in spec files** when a page object exists or should exist.
- **Never put locators in step drivers** — locators live in page objects only.
- **Never import page objects in spec files** when a step driver exists — specs use step drivers.
- **Never rely on test order** — each `test()` must work independently.
- **Never skip cleanup** — every created resource must be tracked for deletion.
- **Never use `cy.exec` equivalents** (`child_process`) — use `KubernetesClient`.
- **Never ignore `xit` blocks** — migrate as `test.fixme()` with Jira link, or implement if the skip reason is resolved.
